4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under the state constitution, if the office of
6 Governor becomes vacant for any reason, the Lieutenant
7 Governor becomes Governor, and if both the office of
8 Governor and Lieutenant Governor become vacant more
9 than 60 days before a general election at which state
10 officers are elected, a Governor and Lieutenant
11 Governor shall be elected at that election for the
12 unexpired term. The state constitution also provides
13 for the order of succession of state officers to serve
14 as Governor during any vacancy of both Governor and
15 Lieutenant Governor.
16 This bill would propose an amendment to the
17 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to provide that if the
18 office of Lieutenant Governor becomes vacant more than
19 60 days before a general election at which state
20 officers are elected, a Lieutenant Governor shall be
21 elected at that election for the unexpired term.
